## Safety nets

1. Feature flags OFF by default until staging sign-off
2. `npm run smoke` before deploy
3. `FEATURE_SHADOW_MODE=true` for validator/catalog compare logs
4. Single-project parity tests in `buyerEnterpriseMultiProject.matrix.test.ts`

## Key files

- Focus: `buyerConversationFocus.service.ts`
- Catalog: `buyerScopedCatalog.service.ts`
- Validator: `buyerOutboundValidator.service.ts`
- Buttons: `buyerButtonScope.service.ts` + `buyerSituationButtons.util.ts`
- Visits: `liveLeadContext.service.ts` + `visitMutationFromChat.service.ts`
- Interactive: `whatsappInteractivePersist.service.ts`

## Activate in staging (all layers)

```
FEATURE_SHADOW_MODE=true
FEATURE_MULTI_VISIT_CONTEXT=true
FEATURE_BUYER_FOCUS_STACK=true
FEATURE_SCOPED_PROPERTY_RESOLVE=true
FEATURE_SCOPED_AI_CATALOG=true
FEATURE_VISIT_DISAMBIGUATION=true
FEATURE_BUTTON_SCOPE_VALIDATE=true
FEATURE_OUTBOUND_PROPERTY_VALIDATE=true
FEATURE_SECOND_VISIT_POLICY=true
```

Kill any layer instantly: set matching `FEATURE_*=false` on Railway — no redeploy required.

## Enterprise stable definition

| Layer | Stable when |
|-------|-------------|
| Context | System knows which project, property, visit(s) |
| Actions | Book/confirm/cancel never targets wrong visit without asking |
| Buttons | Book Visit / More Info match what was discussed |
| AI text | No prices for properties outside shortlist |
| Safety | Flags + tests + smoke; one layer can be turned off |
| Single-project | Parity with enterprise v2 baseline (MP-08) |
